# Force LF line endings on checkout for every text file, regardless of the
# checking-out machine's OS or local git config. Without this, GitHub's
# `windows-latest` runners (default `core.autocrlf=true`) would silently
# convert every text file to CRLF during `actions/checkout`, which matters
# for two things in particular in `rust/` (see the windows CI job in
# .github/workflows/ci.yml):
#   - `cargo fmt --check`: rustfmt's default `newline_style = "Auto"`
#     follows whatever line endings a file already has, so a CRLF-converted
#     checkout wouldn't even fail loudly here -- it would just silently
#     drift from the LF-normalized style every other platform uses.
#   - `rust/crates/labolabo-core/fixtures/{inputs,expected}/**`: the golden
#     tests (`tests/golden.rs`) do byte-for-byte comparisons between real
#     `git`-command output (always LF-terminated, even on Windows) parsed by
#     this crate and checked-in "expected" fixtures -- a CRLF-converted
#     input fixture would desync the comparison in a confusing way.
* text=auto eol=lf

# SQLite fixture: never text-convert. Git's own binary-detection heuristic
# already catches this (SQLite's file header has a NUL byte well within the
# first-8000-bytes scan), so `text=auto` above should already do the right
# thing here -- this line just makes that intent explicit rather than
# relying on the heuristic.
rust/crates/labolabo-core/fixtures/store/*.db binary
